Predictive Modeling Using Machine Learning
Project Overview

This project uses Machine Learning to predict student marks based on study hours and attendance. A Linear Regression model is trained on sample student data and used to make predictions.

Objective

To build a predictive model that can estimate student performance using historical data and evaluate the model's accuracy.

Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
NumPy
Scikit-Learn
Features
Data preprocessing
Train-test data splitting
Linear Regression model training
Student marks prediction
Model performance evaluation using Mean Squared Error (MSE)
Dataset

The dataset contains:

Hours Studied
Attendance Percentage
Marks Obtained
Workflow
Load dataset
Select input and output features
Split data into training and testing sets
Train Linear Regression model
Predict results on test data
Evaluate model performance
Expected Output

The model predicts student marks based on study hours and attendance and displays the prediction results along with the Mean Squared Error value.

Conclusion

This project demonstrates the implementation of a basic Machine Learning predictive model using Linear Regression. It helps understand data preprocessing, model training, prediction, and evaluation techniques.
